    <main class="legal-main">
        <div class="legal-shell">
            <%- include('partials/breadcrumb', {
                crumbs: [{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]
            }) %>

            <header class="legal-hero">
                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p>How Dora Dora Play collects, uses, and protects personal information across our web platform.</p>
            </header>

            <article class="legal-content">
                <h2>1. Scope</h2>
                <p>This Privacy Policy applies to Dora Dora Play websites, pages, and platform features where this notice is published. By using our services, you acknowledge this policy.</p>

                <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>We may collect technical and usage information such as browser type, device information, IP address, page interactions, and session metadata. If you contact us, we also collect the information included in your message.</p>

                <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>To operate and improve platform performance and reliability.</li>
                    <li>To protect the service against fraud, abuse, and unauthorized access.</li>
                    <li>To respond to support, compliance, and legal inquiries.</li>
                    <li>To measure product quality and improve user experience.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>4. Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
                <p>We and our service partners may use cookies or equivalent technologies for essential functionality, analytics, and advertising. You can manage cookies through your browser settings where supported.</p>

                <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
                <p>Some platform features may involve third-party providers (for example analytics, advertising, or embedded game sources). These providers may process data under their own policies and legal obligations.</p>

                <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>We do not sell personal information. We may share data with trusted service providers, legal authorities when required, and business partners strictly to operate, secure, or comply with applicable law.</p>

                <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We implement technical and organizational safeguards designed to protect confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data. No system is fully risk-free, but we continuously improve our controls.</p>

                <h2>8. Retention</h2>
                <p>We retain data only as long as reasonably required for operational, legal, and security purposes, then delete or anonymize it when no longer needed.</p>

                <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correction, deletion, restriction, objection, or data portability. To submit a request, contact us using the email below.</p>

                <h2>10. Children</h2>
                <p>Our services are not intended for children under the age threshold required by applicable local law. If you believe a child provided personal data inappropriately, contact us to request review and removal.</p>

                <h2>11. Policy Updates</h2>
                <p>We may update this policy periodically to reflect legal, technical, or operational changes. The most recent version is always available on this page.</p>

                <h2>12. Contact</h2>
                <p>For privacy or data requests, contact <a href="mailto:taptapgames.fun@gmail.com">taptapgames.fun@gmail.com</a>.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
